name: Cardinal Quelea
rangeDescription: Southern south sudan, northeastern democratic republic of the congo, uganda, and western kenya southward to central and eastern zambia and central malawi; rare nonbreeding visitor to ethiopia
description: The red head of the breeding male is distinctive. Non-breeding male and female are nondescript streaky brown birds with buffy eyebrows.

name: Andaman Boobook
rangeDescription: Andaman islands
description: A compact owl with brownish face and upperparts. Note the bold, rust-colored streaks running down the underparts.

name: Blyth's Pipit
rangeDescription: Southern siberia to mongolia, china, tibet, and northeastern india
description: A mid-sized pipit with pale brown plumage and a fine, dark bill. Strong streaking on the head, mantle, and back contrasts strongly with the pale edges of the feathers.

name: Dark-billed Cuckoo
rangeDescription: Venezuela to the guianas, brazil, northern argentina, and galapagos
description: Brownish above and buff bellow with a black bill, black bandit mask, and gray crown. The eyering is yellowish and the eyes dark.

name: Crab-Plover
rangeDescription: Coastal northern indian ocean; ranges to madagascar and andaman islands
description: Utterly unmistakable large shorebird: gleaming white adult has a black back, black flight feathers, and a very heavy dark bill, which is used to dispatch crustaceans and other invertebrates. Narrow dark smudge around the eye imparts a sleepy appearance.

name: Crimson-bellied Parakeet
rangeDescription: Brazil (western pará, eastern amazonas, and mato grosso) to northern bolivia
description: Long-tailed parakeet. Has green and blue cheeks, a scaled gray breast, and a conspicuous bright red belly.

name: Bonaparte's Parakeet
rangeDescription: Brazil (west-central amazonia along amazon river at tefe and rio purus)
description: Long-tailed parakeet with a dark brown head, pale cheeks, and a scalloped breast. Note the lack of red on the shoulders and the blue forehead.

name: White-eared Jacamar
rangeDescription: Colombia east of the andes to northeastern peru and western amazonian brazil
description: Chunky-looking bird with a small head and a larger bill than other jacamars, recalling a kingfisher. Chestnut-colored overall with a pinkish-red bill.

name: Australian Painted-Snipe
rangeDescription: Eastern and northern australia; vagrant to tasmania
description: Cryptic wader with long, slightly decurved greenish-yellow bill. Bright white underparts, dark brown head and neck, and streaked olive upperparts, with distinctive curved white line extending from breast through the back.

name: Makira Dwarf-Kingfisher
rangeDescription: Makira (southeastern solomon islands)
description: A small kingfisher with deep purplish-blue upperparts and clean white underparts, a white neck spot, and bright orange legs. Bill is black.
imageCreditName: Lars Petersson | My World of Bird Photography

name: Cerulean Warbler
rangeDescription: Eastern north america; winters mountains of colombia to venezuela and southward in andes to western bolivia
description: Brilliant sky-blue warbler of the high canopy. Prefers mature deciduous forest, either in riparian areas or dry mountain ridge-tops.

name: Spotted Piculet
rangeDescription: Eastern brazil (central maranhão and piauí to southern bahia and northern minas gerais)
description: Tiny woodpecker, quite distinct from most other piculets, although hybrids with White-edged and White-barred Piculets are frequent where ranges overlap. Chestnut plumage with white spots diagnostic.

name: Pygmy Hanging-Parrot
rangeDescription: Sulawesi
description: A tiny, bright green parrot with an orange bill, a slim red throat patch, and a red tail. Juveniles have a yellow bill and lack the throat patch.

name: Madagascar Cuckoo-Hawk
rangeDescription: Woodland and scrub of madagascar
description: Rather nondescript, brown mid-sized raptor. Endemic to Madagascar, where it is found in and around all forest types.

name: Sharp-tailed Ibis
rangeDescription: Llanos of eastern colombia to the guianas and western amazonian brazil
description: A medium-sized wading bird, mostly black with a red bill and legs. Relatively long tail projection imparts a long-bodied appearance which is enhanced by its short legs.

name: American Herring Gull
rangeDescription: Northern north america (alaska to atlantic coast); winters to central america
description: Common and widespread large gull found throughout North America. Adults have a fairly pale gray back, pale eye, and dull pinkish legs.

name: Duchess Lorikeet
rangeDescription: Montane forest of solomon islands
description: Beautiful and unmistakable lorikeet, endemic to the Solomon Islands. Rose-red with green wings and a black-bordered yellow band across the chest.

name: Altai Snowcock
rangeDescription: Open alpine habitats to snowline of far northeastern kazakhstan, southwestern siberia, northern xinjiang, and western and central mongolia
description: A burly brown inhabitant of high mountain passes, meadows, and plains, ranging from the low foothills up to isolated snowy peaks. The only snowcock throughout most of its range; minimal overlap with Himalayan Snowcock in far northwestern China and extreme northeastern Kazakhstan.

name: Santa Marta Parakeet
rangeDescription: Santa marta mountains (northeastern colombia)
description: Long tailed and rather plain parakeet endemic to Colombia’s Santa Marta Mountains. The thick, white eye ring and red blotches on face and breast are its best features.

name: Sierra de Lema Flycatcher
rangeDescription: Tepuis of southern and southeastern venezuela, adjacent northern brazil, and western guyana
description: Small flycatcher restricted to mountains in southeastern Venezuela and adjacent parts of Brazil and Guyana. Plumage is olive with tawny on the breast and lower underparts.
